#  TTRV on Windows 10 Pro

#  Step by step:
	
#	1) Windows key --> 'Control Panel' --> Programs --> Turn Windows feauters on or off.

#	2) Locate Windows Subsystem for Linux on the list, enable it. Click OK.

#	3) Wait until it is installed, reboot your PC.

#	4) Open Store, download and install your preffered Linux distrobution.(I will use Debian)

#	5) Open it with Windows key --> 'debian'.

#	6) Set your new username & password.

#	7) 'sudo apt-get update'

#	8) 'sudo apt-get install git'

#	9) 'sudo apt-get install python3'

#	10) 'sudo apt-get install python3-venv'

#	11) 'sudo apt-get install python3-pip'

#	12) 'sudo git clone https://github.com/tildeclub/ttrv.git'
	
#	13) 'cd ttrv'

#	14) 'sudo python3 -m venv venv'

#	15) 'source venv/bin/activate'

#	16) 'python3 -m pip install -r requirments.txt'

#	17) 'deactivate'

#	18) 'sudo python3 setup.py install'

#	19) Open ~/.bashrc , (browser of your choice)paste:    export BROWSER='/mnt/c/Program Files (x86)/Microsoft/Edge/Application/msedge.exe'

#	20) 'ttrv'   && ENJOY TTRV <3
